# JavaScript Classes Overview

## Simple Class Example

```javascript
// Define a class
class Animal {
    constructor(name, species) {
        this.name = name;
        this.species = species;
    }

    speak() {
        return `${this.name} makes a noise.`;
    }
}

// Create an instance of the class
const dog = new Animal('Rover', 'Dog');
console.log(dog.speak()); // Rover makes a noise.
```

### Class Structure:

| Component | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| Constructor | Initializes properties |
| Method | Function within a class |
| Instance | Created object |

# JavaScript Class Inheritance

## Inheritance Example

```javascript
// Parent class
class Animal {
    constructor(name) {
        this.name = name;
    }

    speak() {
        return `${this.name} makes a noise.`;
    }
}

// Child class
class Dog extends Animal {
    constructor(name, breed) {
        super(name);
        this.breed = breed;
    }

    bark() {
        return `${this.name} barks.`;
    }
}

const beagle = new Dog('Snoopy', 'Beagle');
console.log(beagle.speak()); // Snoopy makes a noise.
console.log(beagle.bark());  // Snoopy barks.
```

