# JavaScript Static Methods and Properties

## Static Example

```javascript
class MathUtility {
    static add(a, b) {
        return a + b;
    }

    static get pi() {
        return 3.14159;
    }
}

// Using static methods and properties
console.log(MathUtility.add(1, 2)); // 3
console.log(MathUtility.pi); // 3.14159
```

### Features Table:

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Static Method | Class utility functions |
| Static Property | Class property without instantiation |
| Access Method | Directly via class name |
